00:39.148 --> 00:43.852
Good. He's doing you a
favor, Kimber. It's a gift.

00:46.555 --> 00:49.220
Marcy Hamill flat-lined in recovery.

00:49.288 --> 00:51.390
Why do the police have to know?

00:51.458 --> 00:53.829
No way, Christian. We're not
going down that road again.

00:53.896 --> 00:57.836
This time we do it by the book.

01:04.879 --> 01:13.353
It's not like these are things that I don't
like about you. It's just that, you know...

01:13.420 --> 01:16.584
I mean, there comes a point

01:16.651 --> 01:20.554
where the... the lack of
attention, you know, doesn't

01:20.622 --> 01:23.624
feel like just some sort of
benign neglect. I mean, I know

01:23.692 --> 01:24.658
all about that. My mother was an

01:24.726 --> 01:30.131
expert, trust me. But it begins
to feel intentional, like he...

01:30.198 --> 01:34.668
Like you want to hurt me. But we
have talked about this 50 times.

01:34.736 --> 01:39.240
Didn't we have the same
conversation two weeks ago?

01:39.307 --> 01:41.342
For God's sake, talk, Ron,

01:41.409 --> 01:44.111
because you know that I'll fill
the silences if you don't, and

01:44.179 --> 01:49.283
it's usually with some stupid
crap. And this is exactly what

01:49.351 --> 01:52.753
the doctor and I are talking
about. You need to start

01:52.821 --> 02:01.895
generating this relationship. Ron?

02:01.963 --> 02:04.898
Anything?

02:04.966 --> 02:05.832
I'm done.

02:05.900 --> 02:08.735
Done talking about this?

02:08.803 --> 02:12.439
Done talking about anything.

02:17.845 --> 02:19.779
What is that?

02:19.847 --> 02:22.649
Divorce papers. I had Eddie
draw them up. I've also

02:22.717 --> 02:24.017
separated our bank accounts and

02:24.084 --> 02:26.819
I'm renting a place down in
the marina for the time being.

02:26.887 --> 02:31.257
Tonya's at our place
now, packing up my things.

02:35.128 --> 02:39.064
Dahlia, this is obviously
very painful to hear.

02:39.132 --> 02:45.537
